        "comment": "The wind slabs of last week represent the main danger. As a consequence of new snow and strong wind the avalanche prone locations will become more prevalent. They can be released very easily. These have formed especially in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain. Weak layers exist in the old snowpack on northwest, north and northeast facing slopes. Avalanches can be triggered in the old snowpack reach large size in particular on northwest, north and northeast facing slopes. <br/> Snow sport activities outside marked and open pistes call for experience and great restraint.",
